Mrs. Moya is a very pleasant 68-year-old white female who was diagnosed in April of this year with an adenocarcinoma of the transverse colon.  She underwent segmental transection of the transverse colon by Dr. Morgan April 22.  She presented with bright-red blood per rectum.  They were able to investigate the entire colon on the initial colonoscopy on April 15.
Mrs. Moya has done quite well from her recovery from her surgery.  Is having normal bowel movements.  Eating normally now.

